</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1390,2329,2504,2538]" pageId="262" pageNumber="867" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="262.[1389,2596,1795,2696]" box="[1390,2329,2504,2538]" pageId="262" pageNumber="867">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1390,2090,2504,2538]" pageId="262" pageNumber="867">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="262" pageNumber="867" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="262.[1389,2596,1795,2696]" pageId="262" pageNumber="867">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1391,1748,2544,2578]" pageId="262" pageNumber="867">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Critically Endangered on The IUCN Red List. Known distribution of the Lampobatang Hill Ratis barely over 100 km?, and although it is common there, its population has apparently decreased.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
