</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="263" pageNumber="868" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="263.[166,1374,297,1316]" pageId="263" pageNumber="868">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,523,1129,1158]" pageId="263" pageNumber="868">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Vulnerable on The IUCN Red List. The Northeastern Peninsula Hill Rat has a restricted distribution, and it does occur in Bogani Nani Watarbone National Park. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hatt" authorityYear="1934" box="[627,709,1203,1237]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Thamnomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="263" pageNumber="868" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">Major</taxonomicName>
threats included habitat loss from agricultural expansion and probably gold mining;it is also hunted for food.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
